## [ Parameters ](/documentation/Security/sec_protocol_metadata_access_supported_signature_algorithms(_:_:)#parameters)

`metadata`A `sec_protocol_metadata_t` instance.

`handler`A block to invoke one or more times with OCSP data

## [Return Value](/documentation/Security/sec_protocol_metadata_access_supported_signature_algorithms(_:_:)#return-value)

Returns true if the supported signature list was accessible, false otherwise.

## [Discussion](/documentation/Security/sec_protocol_metadata_access_supported_signature_algorithms(_:_:)#discussion)

Get the signature algorithms supported by the peer. Clients may call this in response to a challenge block.
